The issue is in *what* you return from `page.evaluate()`:

    const maxPage = await root.evaluate(()=&gt; {
        return document.querySelector(
          &quot;li.artdeco-pagination__indicator:nth-last-Child(1)&quot;
        );
    });

This is a DOM node, which is a complex object that cannot be [serialized](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON/stringify#Description), and the return value **must be** serializable in order to be returned back to node from Chromium.

So to fix that and all the future scripts just return only what is needed and what can be `JSON.stringify`ed without error. As pguardiario correctly noted in the comment, in this case it&#39;s enough to return `innerText` from that node:

    const maxPage = await root.evaluate(()=&gt; {
      return document.querySelector(&quot;li.artdeco-pagination__indicator:nth-last-Child(1)&quot;).innerText;
    });

